    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) <strong>half </strong>your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Finely chop (or grate) the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>black olives</strong> into quarters</p><p>Crumble your <strong>feta</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>capers</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pot with the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped olives</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the garlic is fragrant and crispy</p><p>Once crisp, transfer to a bowl and set aside until serving (reserve the pot!) \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy puttanesca oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wipe the reserved pot clean</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once the onion and pepper have softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> of <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> to the pan with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>tuna</strong></p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>drained tuna </strong>and <strong>cooked pasta </strong>to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up until everything is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>tomatoey</strong> <strong>tuna & pepper pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-tuna-and-pepper-pasta-with-crispy-puttanesca-oil/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomatoey</strong> <strong>tuna & pepper pasta</strong> and top with the <strong>crumbled feta</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>crispy puttanesca oil </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave off the crispy puttanesca oil or just add a little!</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
